remote lauching:

.bashrc stuff

source /opt/ros/kinetic/setup.bash
source ~/catkin_ws/devel/setup.bash
export ROS_MASTER_URI=http://master's_IP:11311
export ROS_HOSTNAME=this_comp's_IP

rostopic pub -r10 /hello std_msgs/String "hello"

ufw allow 11311

ssh-keygen -F IP to find if IP key
ssh-keygen -R IP to remove IP key

Master

ssh into the robot to get the proper key set in known_hosts using

ssh user@ip -oHostKeyAlgorithms='ssh-rsa'

create and push a rsa key from the master computer to each robot
ssh-keygen -t rsa

(follow the steps for the key generation)

ssh-copy-id -i (~/path/to/yourPrivatekey) (robot's Username)@(robot's IP address)


copy fail
/etc/ssh/sshd_config

PermitRootLogin yes

sudo passwd

set unix password

